# SQL.txt Documentation

## When to Update

- **On feature completion** — Update Getting Started paths (CLI, WASM, Embedding), API docs, CLI reference, feature docs; include examples for all implementation types where the feature applies
- **On API change** — Update XML comments and generated docs
- **On CLI change** — Update docs/cli-reference.md and examples

## Multi-Implementation Examples

When adding or documenting a feature, update reference docs to show **all applicable implementation types**:

- **CLI (filesystem)** — `sqltxt exec --db ./Db "..."`
- **CLI (WASM)** — `sqltxt exec --db ./Db.wasmdb --wasm "..."`
- **Embedding (C#)** — `await engine.ExecuteAsync(...)`

For each functionality, include examples for each type where the feature applies. Do not document only one implementation path.

## Required Content

- **Getting Started** — Prerequisites, build, minimal example, next steps
- **Public API** — XML docs for all public types/members (purpose, params, returns, exceptions)
- **CLI Reference** — Command syntax, options, examples, exit codes
- **Feature docs** — Per-feature sections with usage of related features

## Locations

- docs/getting-started.md (intro)
- docs/getting-started/cli.md, wasm.md, embedding.md (per-path)
- docs/cli-reference.md
- docs/architecture/05-documentation-standards.md
- docs/architecture/09-wasm-storage.md
- docs/samples/wiki-database.md
